article.description: Sheryl Swoopes scored 16 of her game-high 20 points in the final 10 minutes, helping the Comets break open a close game and defeat the Sting 67-55.
article.headline: Swoopes scores 16 points in final 10 minutes
article.linkText: Swoopes leads second-half Comets charge past Sting
article.story:
CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Sheryl Swoopes gave the Houston Comets just the spark they needed.

Swoopes scored 16 of her game-high 20 points in the final 10 minutes, helping the Comets break open a close game and defeat the Charlotte Sting 67-55 on Sunday.

"Once I hit a couple of shots, I kind of got out the little funk I was in," Swoopes said.

Michelle Snow added 17 points for the Comets (11-7), while Janeth Arcain chipped in with 13. The Comets moved just two games behind Western Conference-leading Sacramento.

Tammy Sutton-Brown led the Sting (3-15) with 14 points, while Allison Feaster scored 12 and Tangela Smith added nine.

Swoopes, who came in averaging 18.5 points per game, was quiet in the first half, scoring only two points. With the game tied at 49, Swoopes began to take over.

After missing the second half of a 1-and-1, Swoopes got her own rebound and put it back to give the Comets a three-point lead with just under eight minutes to play.

Two possessions later, Swoopes stole a pass at the top of the key and drove the length of the floor for a layup and drew a foul. She missed the free throw, but she came up with a loose ball and scored again to extend the lead to 58-49.

Swoopes added another driving layup and two more jumpers to bury the Sting.

"In the second half we had to come out and be a lot more aggressive on offense," Swoopes said. "I was allowing the defense to do pretty much whatever and I needed to be more aggressive. I think they had a tough time deciding how they were going to defend it. "

Swoopes finished 9-of-15 from the field and had six steals and four assists after a slow start.

"That is why she is a superstar, an All-Star," Sting coach Trudi Lacey said. "It's nice to have someone like that who can carry you down the stretch."

It didn't help that the Sting made only one field goal in the final 7:23, that coming with two seconds left in the game.

The Sting got a big first half from Smith and led by as many as eight before taking a 28-23 lead at the break.
